These are existing design system styles and files. Please utilize them alongside base components to build. 

DO NOT allow users to change the underlying theme and primatives of the design system by default. If a user deliberately asks to change the design system, warn the user and only proceed upon acknowledgement.

## **Typography**

Use Tailwind’s text scale paired with font-sans. Map content roles to class names. Do **not** define custom pixel values.

| Text Role | Class |
| ----- | ----- |
| H1 | text-3xl font-semibold leading-tight |
| H2 | text-2xl font-semibold |
| H3 | text-xl font-semibold |
| Body | text-base leading-6 |
| Small | text-sm leading-5 |
| Labels/Buttons | text-sm font-medium uppercase |

Always use font-semibold for headings and font-medium for buttons.

Avoid custom pixel values (e.g., 36px) and square bracket notation.

## **Layout, Spacing & Sizing**

* Use Tailwind's 8px spacing scale only (space-y-4, gap-2, p-6, mt-6, etc.)  
* Never use custom pixel brackets (e.g., p-\[10px\], h-\[40px\], w-\[24px\]) \- only use scale-based utilities  
* Form inputs: h-10 (default), h-8 (compact)  
* Modals: pt-10 pb-14  
* Cards: rounded-sm shadow-sm  
* Use Tailwind utilities only (no custom classnames or values)  
* Use Tailwind’s responsive grid and flexbox utilities

